// Section 11: Conclusion
// =============================================================================

#import "../defs.typ": lean
= Conclusion <sec-conclusion>

A turn is the exercise of an attenuable, proof-carrying token over owned state,
leaving a verifiable receipt. From that one sentence the system follows: four
substances under four disciplines, eight verbs as their structural rules with
minimality a theorem, authority as constructive knowledge produced under a
non-forgeability law, one predicate algebra at four polarities with two computed
prices, and a receipt *Q* that is witness, projection, fold, and light-client
claim at once.

The guarantees are not asserted about an idealized protocol; they are theorems
about the Lean kernel the node runs, pinned to three axioms over an eight-carrier
floor. Authority is unforgeable and non-amplifying; value conserves exactly;
a receipt binds the whole post-state; spends are fresh; and a light client
holding one root learns all of this for the entire history while re-executing
nothing and trusting no executor
(#lean("RecursiveAggregation.light_client_verifies_whole_history")). A server
that ran the protocol wrong cannot produce a verifying aggregate; the pale ghost
has no proof.

That is the one check a stranger makes, and it is the whole of what they must
trust.
